"initial_complaint_text": "Complaint:\n\nI am filing this retaliation complaint about how HACC handled my situation after I raised concerns and tried to use the grievance process. I made a complaint about my housing conditions and asked for help, and shortly after that I started receiving adverse actions from HACC. It feels like I was targeted because I spoke up.\n\nWhat happened, in my own words: I contacted HACC to report issues in my unit and asked for a grievance because I disagreed with HACC’s action and their failure to fix the problem. After that, I received notices and decisions that seemed unrelated to my original issue and were harmful to me. The timing and pattern make it feel like retaliation. I asked for a fair grievance hearing and due process, but I did not feel I was given a meaningful chance to explain my side or appeal before the action was taken.\n\nThis has affected me a lot. It has caused stress, fear about my housing stability, and a sense that I can’t safely raise concerns without being punished. I am trying to follow HACC’s policies and use the grievance process, but I feel shut down and threatened for doing so.\n\nKey facts:\n- I raised a complaint about my housing situation and requested a grievance.\n- Soon after, HACC took adverse actions against me.\n- I asked for an appeal or hearing and did not feel due process was provided.\n- The retaliation has impacted my housing security and wellbeing.\n\nI am asking HACC to stop the retaliatory actions, provide a fair grievance hearing, and follow its own policies regarding tenant disputes and due process. I want a clear explanation of the actions taken against me and a chance to be heard without fear of further retaliation.",
"conversation_history": [
{
"role": "complainant",
"type": "initial_complaint",
"content": "Complaint:\n\nI am filing this retaliation complaint about how HACC handled my situation after I raised concerns and tried to use the grievance process. I made a complaint about my housing conditions and asked for help, and shortly after that I started receiving adverse actions from HACC. It feels like I was targeted because I spoke up.\n\nWhat happened, in my own words: I contacted HACC to report issues in my unit and asked for a grievance because I disagreed with HACC’s action and their failure to fix the problem. After that, I received notices and decisions that seemed unrelated to my original issue and were harmful to me. The timing and pattern make it feel like retaliation. I asked for a fair grievance hearing and due process, but I did not feel I was given a meaningful chance to explain my side or appeal before the action was taken.\n\nThis has affected me a lot. It has caused stress, fear about my housing stability, and a sense that I can’t safely raise concerns without being punished. I am trying to follow HACC’s policies and use the grievance process, but I feel shut down and threatened for doing so.\n\nKey facts:\n- I raised a complaint about my housing situation and requested a grievance.\n- Soon after, HACC took adverse actions against me.\n- I asked for an appeal or hearing and did not feel due process was provided.\n- The retaliation has impacted my housing security and wellbeing.\n\nI am asking HACC to stop the retaliatory actions, provide a fair grievance hearing, and follow its own policies regarding tenant disputes and due process. I want a clear explanation of the actions taken against me and a chance to be heard without fear of further retaliation."
},
